I’ve narrowed it down to the logging configuration, not the TypeScript launcher: the CLI starts `java -jar ...`, and the Chinese text is produced correctly in Kotlin, but the file appenders in the shared Logback configs don’t declare a charset. On Windows that means they fall back to the local code page and corrupt UTF-8 text.

