Done: I fixed Browser4 file-log encoding by adding `<charset>UTF-8</charset>` to every file appender encoder in:

`pulsar-core/pulsar-resources/src/main/resources/logback.xml`

`pulsar-core/pulsar-resources/src/main/resources/logback-dev.xml`

`pulsar-core/pulsar-resources/src/main/resources/logback-prod.xml`

Why: `Browser4AgentsApplication` logs Chinese text like `使用 Web UI`, and the file appenders were inheriting the Windows default code page, causing mojibake in `pulsar.log`.

Validated with:

`.\mvnw.cmd -f pulsar-core\pulsar-resources\pom.xml -DskipTests install`

`.\mvnw.cmd -f browser4\browser4-agents\pom.xml -DskipTests package`

Then I launched `Browser4.jar` with forced `GBK` and confirmed `pulsar.log` still contained `使用 Web UI` correctly.

